In the years since we've moved from the area, Mary's continues to be the point of reference my friend and I use for breakfast. In a later neighborhood we found a pretty good cafe, with roughly similar breakfast -- though not quite as satisfying -- offerings, and we took to calling that place "Fake Mary's." Every now and then when I make an acceptable egg-and-cheese sandwich, she compliments me: "Mm, almost as good as Fake Mary's." But why settle for Fake Mary's when you can have the original? They deliver! Only real downsides: it seems like they're never open when you want them to be; and like most restaurants in the area it's not really a place you go to. Take out, delivery; it's all good. It's all about the food, not the atmosphere.
